column1: # SOURCE: Derived from pv_systems-research.csv and daily_weather_openfield-research.csv
# DESCRIPTION: Daily PV energy output per hectare for low/medium/high density agri-PV systems

# LOGIC: Energy = GHI * panel_area_per_ha * module_efficiency * tilt_factor * irradiance_factor * temp_derate * (1 - system_losses/100) * shading_factor. Cell temp estimated as (T_max+T_min)/2 + temp_adjustment_c. Temp derate = 1 + temp_coeff * (T_cell - T_ref).

# ASSUMPTIONS: (1) Cell temperature approximated from daily avg air temp + density-dependent offset. (2) GHI used as proxy for plane-of-array irradiance (tilt_factor applied as multiplier). (3) No hourly decomposition â€” daily totals only.
